Bounding Rectangle: Given a set of points, P = { (x1, y2)(x2,y2).....(xn,yn) }, 
return the boundary rectangle defined by R = { (xmin,ymax),(xmax,ymin) }



Pseudo Code:

int xMin = -1, xMax = -1, yMin = -1, ymax = -1

xMin = P[0][0];
yMin = P[0][1];

foreach (item in P)
    if (item[0] > xMin)
        xMax = item[0]
    else if (item[0] < xMin)
        xMin = item0
    
    if (item[1] > yMin)
        yMax = item[1]
    else if (item[1] < yMin)
        yMin = item[1]

    
